enhanced_by.reason: The unmodifiableMap method initializes the map that is used by the values method to return an unmodifiable collection of values.
The entrySet method initializes the entry set of the map, which is related to the values method as it indirectly provides access to the values collection.
The readObject method deserializes the map, which is necessary to have a valid map state before calling the values method.
The writeObject method serializes the map, which is related to the values method as it ensures the map state is preserved before serialization.
